\b\fc1\cf1 Object of the Game\

\b0\fs8 \

\fs24\fc0\cf0 Be the first player to correctly determine the murderer, weapon, and location of the crime.\
\

\b\fc1\cf1 Beginning the Game\

\b0\fs8 \

\fs24\fc0\cf0 The suspects, weapons, and rooms are each represented by one card from a deck of twenty-one cards.  At the start of the game, a suspect, a weapon and a room are chosen from the deck as the solution to the murder, and hidden.  The remaining cards are dealt to the players.  These cards are used to disprove other players' suggestions.\

\fs12\fc1\cf1 \

\fs24\fc0\cf0 Each player chooses a suspect as their playing piece.  Players take turns moving their pieces and making suggestions.  Scarlet goes first, and play proceeds clockwise around the board.\
\

\b\fc1\cf1 Moving\

\b0\fs8 \

\fs24\fc0\cf0 At the start of each turn you must decide how to proceed.  Your options are:
\i \

\i0\fs12\fc1\cf1 \

\i\fs24\fc0\cf0 Roll
\i0  \

\pard\li360\fc0\cf0 You can roll the die and move your piece through the corridors or into a room.  You can move up, down, left, or right, but not diagonally.  You cannot move through any square occupied by an opponent, nor can you pass through the same corridor square more than once in a single turn.  You cannot re-enter a room that you left in the same turn.  You do not need an exact roll to enter a room, but you must use the entire die roll if you stop in the corridor.\

\pard\tx520\tx1060\tx1600\tx2120\tx2660\tx3200\tx3720\tx4260\tx4800\tx5320\fs12\fc1\cf1 \

\i\fs24\fc0\cf0 Passage
\i0 \

\pard\li360\fc0\cf0 Each corner room has a secret passage to the room in the opposite corner.  If you are in a corner room at the start of your turn, you can take the secret passage to the room in the opposite corner 
\i instead
\i0  of rolling the die.\

\pard\tx520\tx1060\tx1600\tx2120\tx2660\tx3200\tx3720\tx4260\tx4800\tx5320\fs12\fc1\cf1 \

\i\fs24\fc0\cf0 Stay
\i0 \

\pard\li360\fc0\cf0 If your piece was transferred into a room by an opponent's suggestion, then you can stay in the room and make a suggestion, 
\i instead
\i0  of moving.\

\pard\tx520\tx1060\tx1600\tx2120\tx2660\tx3200\tx3720\tx4260\tx4800\tx5320\fc0\cf0 \

\b\fc1\cf1 Entering and Leaving Rooms\

\b0\fs8 \

\fs24\fc0\cf0 You must enter a room to make a suggestion in that room.  You can enter a room by rolling the die and passing through a door; by taking a secret passage; or by getting transferred into the room by an opponent's suggestion.  After making a suggestion in a room, you must leave the room and enter it again before you can make another suggestion there.\
\

